<TEXT>
authorities searched tuesday for seven 
children one possibly as young as 6 who surrounded two sailors 
in a parking lot and held them up with a westernstyle pistol 
police said 
the sailors were too startled late sunday by the big handgun 
clutched with both hands by one of the children who appeared to be 
the oldest at 13 or 14 to provide police with a detailed 
description of the group 
the youngest of the children appeared to be 6 or 7 
they couldnt give good descriptions because they were looking 
at a large westernstyle gun you know like cowboys and indians 
the old longbarreled pistol said orlando police lt mike 
mankins 
every indication was that it was real he said of the gun 
the youngsters ran off after the holdup 
the sailors mark beazley 19 and john russell 18 were on 
their way from a movie theater to the orlando naval training center 
when they were surrounded in the theater parking lot by the 
children who demanded money police said 
the youngsters only got a few dollars from the sailors wallets 
mankins said 
one of the boys clubbed beazley over the head but he wasnt 
seriously hurt police said 
