the defense department has delayed announcing 
a white houseapproved plan to involve us military forces more 
deeply in the international war on drugs a spokesman said tuesday 
some of the aspects of that have been put off for a while 
following discussions with colombian president barco pentagon 
spokesman pete williams told reporters as he announced that the 
department will not hold a news conference this week on the drug 
plan as planned 
williams said he expected an announcement on the drug plan after 
the department releases its budget for fiscal 1991 on jan 29 he 
said he was unsure whether it would be announced before president 
bush goes to colombia in february for an antidrug summit of the 
leaders of andean nations 
under the reported antidrug effort the navy was to operate an 
aircraft carrier battle group off the caribbean coast of colombia 
on a rotating basis 
pentagon officials have said the navy would use hightech radar 
and surveillance equipment to keep tabs on suspected drug dealers 
boats and planes 
peru colombia and bolivia have said they oppose the use of us 
military to police international waters 
defense department sources said a week ago that the aircraft 
carrier john f kennedy would lead the interdiction effort the 
carrier returned to floridas mayport naval station on tuesday 
