<TEXT>
hilda the hippo en route to a reunion 
with her mate harvey escaped from her truck on a busy highway but 
her brief taste of freedom ended in death 
the truck hilda was traveling in jackknifed on a busy highway at 
thruxton in hampshire 65 miles west of london and the threeton 
hippopotamus escaped 
she ambled along the highway nibbling at the grass and even 
managed a quick nap as passing motorists blinked in disbelief 
several swerved to miss hitting her 
but experts said the stress of the accident and the trauma of 
being hauled into another trailer after being knocked out with a 
sedative proved too much for the 10yearold hippo who died 
shortly after her recapture 
local veterinarian geraint griffiths said the problem was that 
it was impossible to get hilda into the new trailer quickly and 
give her an early antidote to the sedative because of her sheer 
weight 
hilda was being transferred from longleat safari park in 
wiltshire to windsor safari park where she was to join harvey 
i think she jumped up and tried to turn round and that turned 
the trailer over said her driver mike vandy 
griffiths was called in to sedate hilda with a tranquilizing 
dart so she could be caught and put in a replacement truck 
but it took an hour of heaving and pushing to lift hilda into 
the truck and the difficult operation was only completed after a 
vehicle normally used for lifting heavy commercial vehicles was 
called in to help 
a hampshire police spokesman speaking anonymously said she 
was extremely wellbehaved and docile its a great shame to hear 
that she has died 
</TEXT>
