<TEXT>
one of every 80 east germans worked or 
informed for the secret police and 3200 employees did nothing but 
tap telephones and open mail according to the official assigned to 
dismantle the dreaded agency 
manfred sauer said the huge state security apparatus cost 36 
billion marks last year the equivalent of 2 billion at the 
official rate of the time 
that was 13 percent of the entire national budget sauer told 
the seventh weekly negotiating session between the communists and 
opposition on monday he spoke just hours before tens of thousands 
of people ransacked security police headquarters in east berlin 
