power has been criticized by the current government for his forced 
collectivization policies and his bureaucratic centralism 
mongolia a nation of 2 million people spread across the vast 
deserts and grasslands of eastern asia has cautiously followed the 
reform policies taken by its protector state the soviet union 
however the government has said the pace of reform has been too 
slow and members of parliament have called for fundamental changes 
in price and wage systems in the statecontrolled economy 
the source said it was not clear whether political upheaval in 
east europe was influencing events in distant mongolia and it was 
probably wrong to rush toward expectations of dramatic changes 
in the country 
