<TEXT>
the supreme court today left intact a 156 
million award against a montana religious group sued by a former 
member 
the court without comment rejected arguments that the award 
violates the organizations religious freedom 
church universal amp triumphant was sued by gregory mull a 
53yearold san francisco architect when in 1974 he started taking 
part in the churchs activities 
mull who died in 1986 moved in 1979 to calabasas calif site 
of the churchs headquarters at the time known as camelot the 
church moved its headquarters to montana in 1986 
he said elizabeth clare prophet the churchs spiritual leader 
with the title messenger of the ascended masters promised mull 
would help design buildings for the groups proposed 33 million 
new jerusalem in calabasas 
according to court documents the church secretly had abandoned 
the project without telling mull the suit alleged that the church 
was using his architectural plans to help raise millions of dollars 
in donations 
mull also accused the church of violating his privacy rights by 
disclosing details of his sex life given in a confession to 
mrs prophet 
he also sued the church for inflicting emotional distress 
alleging he was pressured into giving up his last 5500 in savings 
at a time when he was out of work and supporting his daughter in 
college 
a california appeals court in upholding the 156 million jury 
award last april said mull was subject to constant and shameful 
pressures to part with his money and that he became so destitute 
he and his daughter took food from grocery store garbage bins 
the daughter linda witt is mulls heir 
the church said the damage award should be overturned because 
in part it was based on prejudicial evidence and ridicule of the 
churchs religious practices by mulls lawyer 
for example the church said mrs prophets husband edward 
francis testifed under questioning by mulls lawyer that he 
believed he was the reincarnation of captain cook 
the lawyer then prefaced the next question by saying let me 
ask you this one as mr francis instead of captain cook 
the church said the jury also was prejudiced by the testimony of 
a witness for mull who said he once had an adulterous affair with 
mrs prophet 
the church said mulls suit was based on the claim he had been 
reduced to a slave of the church the resulting damage award 
constitutes an unprecedented threat to the free exercise of 
religion of minority religious organizations and their members 
the church said 
the justices have rejected two similar appeals recently 
in october they left intact a ruling that an evangelical 
christian group must return 55 million donated by a department 
store heiress when she was a member 
the court last may refused to shield the rev sun myung moons 
unification church from being sued by two former california members 
who said they were brainwashed into joining it 
the case acted on today is church universal amp triumphant vs 
witt 89672 
