the widow of investorpublisher john hay whitney 
will offer a renoir from the couples collection for sale for an 
estimated 40 million to 50 million sothebys auction house said 
tuesday 
pierreauguste renoirs 1876 artwork acclaimed for its light 
shadow and movement depicts the moulin de la galette a french 
outdoor dance hall in montmartre frequented by avantgarde writers 
painters and actors 
it shows a model named estelle siting at a table with three of 
renoirs friends including biographer georges rivere who later 
described the painting as a page of history a precious moment of 
paris life depicted with rigorous examination 
the painting was owned for 60 years by whitney and his wife 
betsey cushing whitney 
whitney who died in 1982 founded jh whitney amp co a 
venturecapitalist firm and was an ambassador to great britain and 
publisher of the new york herald tribune 
he became a trustee of the museum of modern art in 1930 was 
named president in 1941 and was chairman from 1946 to 1956 he was 
a trustee of the national gallery of art in washington from 1961 to 
1979 
a larger version of au moulin de la galette is in the musee 
dorsay in paris it is believed one was painted at the scene and 
the other at renoirs studio but no one knows which is which 
sothebys will take the whitney version to paris for a 
comparison in february then after exhibits in tokyo zurich 
paris and london the renoir will return to new york for an auction 
on may 16 
after whitneys death his wife gave five institutions 20 works 
by edgar degas paul gauguin pablo picasso henri rousseau 
georges seurat james abbott mcneill whistler and other artists 
several other whitneys also are wellknown in the art world 
whitneys niece linda de roulet sold pablo picassos au 
lapin agile a paris tavern scene on nov 17 for 407 million 
mrs de roulets brother john whitney payson sold vincent van 
goghs irises in 1987 for 539 million the highest price ever 
obtained at an art auction 
