in wages preservation of their privileges a decrease in 
administrative personnel and no repercussions for strikers 
the government has adopted a tight wage policy in an effort to 
bring down inflation that soared to about 900 percent last year 
after a partial lifting of price controls last august 
most of the remaining price controls were lifted on jan 1 and 
prices have soared again ahead of wages 
