the power of the national communist party known as the league of 
communists and would grant virtual independence to regional party 
organizations 
it is certain to encounter fierce resistance from hardliners in 
the communist leadership of serbia the largest of yugoslavias six 
constituent republics who still favor strong central control in 
party and state affairs 
the liberal slovenian leadership also reportedly demanded urgent 
changes in electoral laws to fully legalize opposition political 
parties the first democratic multiparty elections in the 
45yearold history of this communist country are tentatively 
planned in slovenia for april 
the proposals came from the slovenian communist partys 
policysetting central committee 
yugoslavia has not formally adopted a law allowing independent 
political parties to form but numerous opposition political groups 
have sprung up throughout the country in the past few months 
yugoslavias communists were the first to break with monolithic 
sovietled communist bloc in 1948 but yugoslavia faced with its 
