<TEXT>
some of the smartest most successful business 
people make the biggest and in retrospect the most foolish 
mistakes mistakes of such magnitude that simpler folks find them 
incomprehensible 
robert campeau a successful canadian developer whose ambition 
for bigger things brought about the bankruptcy court filing of 
federated department stores inc and allied stores corp is the 
latest on a list destined to grow larger 
campeau had what many people would consider everything he 
was highly successful controlling millions of dollars with which 
to indulge himself but he bet it all on something unfamiliar 
retailing and in a foreign country no less 
the explanation for his behavior and the many similarly bright 
people who seem to court disaster might best be explained someday 
by psychological rather than financial analysis but right now it 
is a major mystery 
on the long list are bankers the people you might think should 
know better bankers repeatedly lend money to builders at the wrong 
time in the economic cycle that is when overbuilding is about to 
take place 
bankers also are the decisionmakers who at a time 15 years ago 
when customers couldnt beg a home mortgage lent billions to third 
world nations explaining to simple folks that these loans are 
guaranteed by governments 
it happens often in real estate when successful developers 
eventually come to love and believe the praise they receive at 
groundbreaking ceremonies it lures them into what they believe 
will be their crowning achievement 
so common is the successfailure syndrome in that field that it 
is all but inevitable that sometime somewhere some major 
developer will be caught bringing a commercial building to 
completion just as the market is collapsing 
in stocks and commodities successful speculators let their egos 
talk them into believing they really can see the future a future 
that often involves their biggest deal ever one so sure they cut 
friends in on it 
in business successful small operators get tired of slow 
growth convince themselves that bigger is better borrow madly and 
buy up everything in sight they develop what they call a 
conglomerate each part feeding the other 
financial advisers to corporate raiders dissatisfied with 
earning only commissions see the potential for profit enhancement 
not simply by giving advice but by investing their own money 
too often the result is the same they overstep their abilities 
somehow shielding from consciousness their own failsafe 
mechanisms their instincts and the years of experience that 
brought them their success 
william zeckendorf sr was a flamboyant and successful 
developer famous and feted reputed to be the man to get things 
don when nobody else could he helped put together the land package 
on which the united nations stands 
for years he was honored then he overstepped and failed 
reflecting on his collapsed career he asked a reporter sadly 
did you know they named a park for me in denver the reporter 
checked yes he was told its about the size of a postage 
stamp 
speculators and investment advisers bite the dust all the time 
right after they feel on top of the world the hunt brothers 
garnered a fortune in silver but lost it all when they sought it 
all and joseph granville the investment adviser was so certain 
he knew the future that he missed the crash of 1987 
and there is campeau and his backers all knew that campeau had 
little or no experience in retailing or in the united states 
market and that the risk was so great the deal might collapse if 
sales and profits werent sustained 
they knew also that after one of the longest us economic 
expansions on record a slowdown was inevitable or that at the 
other extreme any reheating of the economy might force up interest 
rates making debt repayment impossible 
those investors included people and institutions who gobbled up 
campeau junk bonds because of the high interest rates even when 
warned again and again that repayment was uncertain 
it included even the investment bankers who issued the warnings 
</TEXT>
