commercial paper business eliminated one equity division at its 
new york headquarters and reduced trading of british stocks 
merrill has slashed about 40 out of 600 jobs in its equities 
trading area and 10 of 130 in equities research this month 
brokerage firms across wall street have suffered because of 
overcapacity stemming from precrash days and too little business 
more than 23000 jobs have been cut on wall street in a 
retrenchment since the crash 
despite strong stock and bond markets last year the industry 
has been in a downturn in part because of an exodus by individual 
investors and a decline in businesses such as investment banking 
merrill is one of the powerhouses on the street keefe said 
they have just about every business there and business is in a 
