<TEXT>
business sales and inventories both rose in 
november the government said tuesday but economists noted that 
slower sales the following month could worsen the december 
situation 
the commerce department said inventories rose 05 percent to a 
seasonally adjusted 7968 billion in november after rising 03 
percent a month earlier the november figure was slightly higher 
than the 04 percent increase originally reported 
business sales were up 07 percent to a seasonally adjusted 
5236 billion after falling a revised 05 percent in october 
that revision compared with the initially reported 07 percent drop 
inventories often rise during periods of slow economic growth 
and could result in production cutbacks and loss of jobs as 
businesses try to reduce the accumulation of goods on shelves and 
backlots such activity is taking place in the auto industry for 
example as carmakers try to shrink bloated inventories with 
production cuts and layoffs 
retail sales were relatively modest in december said 
evelina tainer senior domestic economist for the first national 
bank of chicago autos were still weak so theres a potential 
for the inventoriestosales ratio number to worsen 
the november business activity caused the ratio of inventories 
to sales to decline slightly to 152 meaning it would take 152 
months to exhaust inventories at the november pace the ratio was 
153 in october 
ms tainer did not consider the ratio to be alarming saying it 
was relatively low compared to 10 years ago 
producers used to keep more inventories and i think they have 
become leaner she said so were not in the same problem area 
that we would have been several years ago 
ms tainer said the inventory problems that do exist are 
concentrated in certain areas such as automobiles 
chrysler co ford motor co and general motors corp all have 
announced temporary layoffs to reduce their vehicle inventories 
mazda motor corp of japan also is trimming production at its us 
plant this month 
retail inventories rose 06 percent in november while sales 
increased 05 percent the commerce department reported last week 
that retail sales gained only 02 percent in december 
inventories at the manufacturing level which represent about 45 
percent of the total rose 03 percent manufacturing sales 
increased 05 percent 
wholesalers inventories advanced 05 percent while their sales 
jumped 12 percent 
overall inventories were 68 percent above those of a year ago 
while sales were up 44 percent 
</TEXT>
