<TEXT>
east germanys economics minister on 
tuesday conceded two more exceptions to jointventure regulations 
that will allow numerous west german firms to hold majority shares 
economics minister christa luft told reporters after her talks 
with west german counterpart helmut haussmann that small and 
mediumsized companies as well as those large firms with superb 
knowhow will be allowed to become majority owners 
the east german parliament approved draft regulations on friday 
that established 49 percent as the upper limit for foreign 
ownership of enterprises in east germany 
east germans fear that allowing foreign companies especially 
wealthy and influential west german industrial giants to hold 
majority ownership could lead to a buyout of the economically 
troubled state struggling toward democracy 
but west german firms have rejected the 49 percent limit as too 
restrictive and insufficient to attract the major infusions of 
capital east germany needs to turn around its stagnant economy 
ms luft said east germany plans to retain the 49 percent 
ceiling in principle but that exceptions will be made 
east german openness to exceptions for firms with special 
technical knowhow appears to open a wide door for west germanys 
numerous aerospace computer chemical and engineering firms that 
are seeking to establish themselves in the reformminded nation 
next door 
hundreds of small familyrun companies have expressed interest 
in setting up intergerman ventures but only on condition that 
they own controlling interest in the companies 
an influential delegation of west german industrialists traveled 
to east berlin over the weekend for talks with ms luft communist 
premier hans modrow and other officials and political leaders for 
talks on how to boost business ties 
edzard reuter chairman of the daimlerbenz conglomerate that is 
west germanys largest company and one of the biggest defense and 
technology firms in the world told reporters after the visit that 
the 49 percent limit was businesswise and psychologically wrong 
ms luft and haussmann said they made good progress in closing 
gaps between east german and west german economic cooperation 
during their talks in bonn 
they announced that a joint committee had been established to 
work out the details of an investment protection agreement 
</TEXT>
