a young entrepreneur who sought control of 
bond corp holdings inc without explaining how he would finance 
his 197 million bid or deal with the australian conglomerates 
immense debt said tuesday he had abandoned his offer 
the statement from jeff h reynolds came five days after bond 
the brewing and media company controlled by millionaire alan bond 
said reynolds did not appear to have the capacity to undertake the 
deal 
bond had said earlier it was willing to talk to reynolds 
beginning with a news release issued jan 5 reynolds said he 
was negotiating to take over bond through his weatherby investments 
inc and its parent singaporebased california pacific 
international holdings co pte ltd 
newspapers and news agencies worldwide ran stories on his 
friendly offer to save bond which was near collapse under a nearly 
6 billion load of debt and related legal problems 
reynolds a 28yearold texan operating out of his mothers 
house in houston claimed he had lined up the 197 million and was 
negotiating financing to service bonds debt 
but checks by the associated press showed that weatherby once 
run by reynolds father lost its corporate charter in nevada in 
1987 after failing to file its annual list of officers the younger 
reynolds was never listed as an officer or director of weatherby 
the address reynolds gave for investors was a mail drop in 
beverly hills he refused to reveal the location in century city 
from which he said his associates were operating and he never 
revealed his source of funds 
he described the lapsed corporate license as a screw up by 
his staff or attorneys and even said he might undertake a hostile 
bid for bond after the company rejected his offer last week 
on tuesday he issued another news release saying his companies 
were withdrawing from negotiations with bond corp mainly 
because of the australian companys legal and financial problems 
last thursday bond corp released a statement from its 
headquarters in perth western australia saying it had been unable 
to obtain information about the proposed cash offer it said 
reynolds bid was doubtful and causing the company considerable 
embarrassment 
it was made very clear to mr reynolds and his associates 
right from the very beginning that there would be no discussions 
until bond corp was satisfied that mr reynolds andor his 
companies have the financial capacity to undertake a transaction of 
the size and nature he proposes bond corp spokesman peter lucas 
said 
in the absence of any such information having been made 
