<TEXT>
the supreme court in one of two suits arising 
from strikes against airlines refused tuesday to allow a 
machinists union walkout at eastern airlines spread to commuter 
railroads 
the court also refused to revive a suit brought by trans world 
airlines flight attendants who accused twa owner carl icahn of sex 
bias in seeking wage cuts and other concessions that triggered a 
1986 strike 
the courts ruling in the eastern case resolved a question left 
by the walkout by the international association of machinists that 
began more than 10 months ago 
the justices without comment left intact lower court decisions 
barring sympathy strikes against railroads in new york city 
philadelphia and their suburbs 
the machinists who walked off the job last march 4 after 
refusing to give more than 150 million in concessions sought by 
eastern remain on strike pilots and flight attendants supported 
the strike for eight months before ending their walkouts in 
november 
the machinists and unions sympathetic to the eastern strike 
