other benefits from the airline 
the independent federation of flight attendants called a strike 
against twa on march 7 1986 two months later the union offered 
to return to work and accept twas demands 
the strike was called when icahn insisted on wage and other 
concessions for attendants 85 percent of them women that were 
greater than cuts he sought to impose against the airlines pilots 
machinists and other workers 
during the negotiations with the attendants union icahn said it 
would be easy for him to find young untrained women to be 
stewardesses for less than he was paying the attendants 
when union negotiators said janitors who belonged to the 
machinists union were offered a better deal than the attendants 
icahn remarked 
a janitor is a breadwinner who probably has got a family at 
home to support while you girls are second incomes and you dont 
need the money 
the union said the statement demonstrated bias against women and 
violated fair bargaining procedures mandated by the federal railway 
labor act which governs labor negotiations for airlines and 
railroads 
